<h1>4. Class Specifications — Create a Request by Client</h1>

<p>This section covers all classes involved in the "Create a Request by Client" feature flow, spanning both Server-side (NestJS) and Client-side (React/TypeScript).</p>

<!-- ===== 4.1 ===== -->
<h2>4.1 ProjectRequestsController Class</h2>

<p><b>Description:</b> REST API controller that handles all HTTP endpoints for the Project Requests module. Uses JwtAuthGuard and RolesGuard for authentication and authorization. Delegates business logic to ProjectRequestsService.</p>

<h3>Class Attributes</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>No</th><th>Attribute</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>01</td><td>projectRequestsService</td><td>ProjectRequestsService</td><td>Injected service instance responsible for all project request business logic. Marked as private readonly.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Class Methods</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>No</th><th>Method</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr>
  <td>01</td>
  <td>async create(userId: string, createDto: CreateProjectRequestDto, req: RequestContext): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity&gt;</td>
  <td>[POST /project-requests] Creates a new project request on behalf of the authenticated client.<br>- Parameter userId: UUID string extracted from the JWT token, identifies the client creating the request.<br>- Parameter createDto: DTO object validated via CreateProjectRequestDto, contains title, description, budgetRange, intendedTimeline, techPreferences, isDraft, and answers[].<br>- Parameter req: The request context object used for audit logging (IP, user-agent).<br>- Returns: The fully populated ProjectRequestEntity with answers, question, and option relations.<br>- Internal: Calls projectRequestsService.create(userId, createDto, req).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>02</td>
  <td>async getProjectRequests(user: UserEntity, status?: string): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity[]&gt;</td>
  <td>[GET /project-requests] Retrieves project requests. If the user role is CLIENT, returns only the client's own requests via findAllByClient(). Otherwise (Admin/Broker), returns all requests optionally filtered by status.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>03</td>
  <td>async findMyDrafts(userId: string): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity[]&gt;</td>
  <td>[GET /project-requests/drafts/mine] Returns all draft-status requests owned by the authenticated user. Calls findDraftsByClient(userId).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>04</td>
  <td>async getOne(id: string, user: UserEntity): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity&gt;</td>
  <td>[GET /project-requests/:id] Retrieves a single project request by UUID. Applies role-based access control: Clients can only view their own; Brokers cannot view requests assigned to other brokers; Freelancers must have an associated proposal.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>05</td>
  <td>async update(id: string, updateDto: UpdateProjectRequestDto): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity&gt;</td>
  <td>[PATCH /project-requests/:id] Updates an existing request (e.g., save draft, change status, update answers). Accepts partial DTO fields.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>06</td>
  <td>uploadFile(files: UploadedFilesMap): object</td>
  <td>[POST /project-requests/upload] Handles multipart file uploads for requirements (max 1) and attachments (max 5). Returns an object with filenames and mock URLs. Uses FileFieldsInterceptor.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>07</td>
  <td>async seedTestData(clientId?: string): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity[]&gt;</td>
  <td>[POST /project-requests/seed-test-data] Seeds test data for UI verification. Creates Phase 3 and Phase 4 test requests.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<!-- ===== 4.2 ===== -->
<h2>4.2 ProjectRequestsService Class</h2>

<p><b>Description:</b> Core business logic service for project requests. Handles CRUD operations, status transitions, broker/freelancer proposals, audit logging, and AI matching integration. Decorated with @Injectable().</p>

<h3>Class Attributes</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>No</th><th>Attribute</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>01</td><td>requestRepo</td><td>Repository&lt;ProjectRequestEntity&gt;</td><td>TypeORM repository injected via @InjectRepository() for CRUD operations on the project_requests table.</td></tr>
<tr><td>02</td><td>answerRepo</td><td>Repository&lt;ProjectRequestAnswerEntity&gt;</td><td>TypeORM repository for CRUD operations on the project_request_answers table.</td></tr>
<tr><td>03</td><td>brokerProposalRepo</td><td>Repository&lt;BrokerProposalEntity&gt;</td><td>TypeORM repository for managing broker proposals/invitations.</td></tr>
<tr><td>04</td><td>freelancerProposalRepo</td><td>Repository&lt;ProjectRequestProposalEntity&gt;</td><td>TypeORM repository for managing freelancer proposals/invitations.</td></tr>
<tr><td>05</td><td>auditLogsService</td><td>AuditLogsService</td><td>Injected service for recording audit logs of create/update actions.</td></tr>
<tr><td>06</td><td>matchingService</td><td>MatchingService</td><td>Injected service for AI-powered broker/freelancer matching.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Class Methods</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>No</th><th>Method</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr>
  <td>01</td>
  <td>async create(clientId: string, dto: CreateProjectRequestDto, req: RequestContext): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity&gt;</td>
  <td>Creates a new project request and its associated answers.<br>- Parameter clientId: UUID of the client user.<br>- Parameter dto: Validated DTO containing title, description, budgetRange, intendedTimeline, techPreferences, isDraft flag, and answers array.<br>- Parameter req: Request context for audit logging.<br>- Processing: (1) Creates ProjectRequestEntity with status DRAFT or PUBLIC_DRAFT based on isDraft. (2) Saves entity to DB. (3) Maps and saves ProjectRequestAnswerEntity[] for each answer. (4) Reloads the full entity with relations. (5) Logs a CREATE audit entry.<br>- Returns: The fully populated ProjectRequestEntity including answers with question/option relations.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>02</td>
  <td>async findAll(status?: RequestStatus): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity[]&gt;</td>
  <td>Retrieves all project requests with relations (answers, client, broker), ordered by createdAt DESC. Optionally filters by RequestStatus enum value.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>03</td>
  <td>async update(id: string, dto: UpdateProjectRequestDto): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity&gt;</td>
  <td>Updates a project request's fields and manages status transitions. Handles PUBLIC to PRIVATE visibility toggle (denies pending broker proposals when switching to private). Updates answers if provided by deleting old ones and creating new entries.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>04</td>
  <td>async findAllByClient(clientId: string): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity[]&gt;</td>
  <td>Returns all requests for a specific client, ordered by createdAt DESC, with answer relations loaded.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>05</td>
  <td>async findDraftsByClient(clientId: string): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity[]&gt;</td>
  <td>Returns only DRAFT-status requests for a specific client.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>06</td>
  <td>async findOne(id: string, user?: UserEntity): Promise&lt;ProjectRequestEntity&gt;</td>
  <td>Retrieves one request with full relations (answers, client, broker, proposals, specs). Applies role-based access control: masks client PII for brokers on PENDING requests, restricts freelancer access to only invited/accepted. Throws NotFoundException or ForbiddenException.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<!-- ===== 4.3 ===== -->
<h2>4.3 CreateProjectRequestDto Class</h2>

<p><b>Description:</b> Data Transfer Object for validating and typing the request body when creating a new project request. Uses class-validator decorators for input validation and @nestjs/swagger decorators for API documentation.</p>

<h3>Class Attributes</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>No</th><th>Attribute</th><th>Type</th><th>Validators</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>01</td><td>title</td><td>string</td><td>@IsNotEmpty(), @IsString()</td><td>The short title of the project request. Required field.</td></tr>
<tr><td>02</td><td>description</td><td>string</td><td>@IsNotEmpty(), @IsString()</td><td>Detailed description of the project idea. Required field.</td></tr>
<tr><td>03</td><td>budgetRange</td><td>string (optional)</td><td>@IsOptional(), @IsString()</td><td>Estimated budget range (e.g., "1K_5K"). Optional.</td></tr>
<tr><td>04</td><td>intendedTimeline</td><td>string (optional)</td><td>@IsOptional(), @IsString()</td><td>Expected completion date or duration. Optional.</td></tr>
<tr><td>05</td><td>techPreferences</td><td>string (optional)</td><td>@IsOptional(), @IsString()</td><td>Comma-separated technology preferences. Optional.</td></tr>
<tr><td>06</td><td>isDraft</td><td>boolean (optional)</td><td>@IsOptional()</td><td>If true, saves as DRAFT; if false or omitted, saves as PUBLIC_DRAFT. Default: false.</td></tr>
<tr><td>07</td><td>answers</td><td>CreateProjectRequestAnswerDto[]</td><td>@IsArray(), @ValidateNested({each: true}), @Type()</td><td>Array of wizard answers, each referencing a question and containing either an optionId or valueText. Required.</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ===== 4.4 ===== -->
<h2>4.4 CreateProjectRequestAnswerDto Class</h2>

<p><b>Description:</b> Nested DTO representing a single wizard answer within the create request payload.</p>

